Reasoning: The paper focuses on analyzing the work patterns and possible indicators of overload and time pressure on software developers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also explores the impact of work patterns on the work-life balance of software engineers, which could be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of mining software repositories approach suggests a focus on data analysis and computational methods, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the study also involves analyzing the content of work during different times of the week, which could be relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
